Deputy National Security Advisor Benjamin J. Rhodes recently met with Vietnamese-American civil society leaders and other non-government leaders working on human rights, governance reform, and rule of law in Vietnam. The meeting aimed to discuss President Obama's upcoming trip to Vietnam. Senior officials from the National Security Council and the Department of State also participated in the meeting. The participants shared their views and ideas on human rights, governance reform, and legal reform, which will help in preparing for the President's trip. The United States continues to emphasize its support for universal values such as inclusive governance, strong civil societies, fair labor practices, and respect for human rights globally.